<section id="About">
<h2>About Chitter</h2>
<p><strong>Chitter</strong> is a British microblogging and social networking service on which users post</p>
<p>and interact with messages.</p>
<p>Registered users can post messages, but unregistered users can only read them.</p>
<p>Users access Chitter through its <strong>website interface</strong>, through Short Message Service (SMS) or </p>
<p>its mobile-device application software ("app").</p>
<p><strong>Chitter, Inc.</strong> is based in <Strong>Shoreditch</strong>, London and has more than 10 offices around the world.</p>
<p>Peeps were originally restricted to 140 characters, but there is currently no limit</p>
<p>Chitter was created in <strong>January 2020</strong> by <strong>Millie Jacobson, Donna Graham and Imelda Danson.</strong> </p>
<p>The service rapidly gained worldwide popularity. </p>
